mpton's Poetic Justice and Zorns Lemma and Morgan Fisher's Standard Gauge, and William Greaves's recently rediscovered Symbiopsychotaxiplasm: Take One. Michael Snow turns film loose on language in So Is This; Peter Rose turns language loose on theory in Pressures of the Text. Some of the most influential feminist filmscripts of recent decades—Laura Mulvey and Peter Wollen's Riddles of the Sphinx, Su Friedrich's Gently Down the Stream, Trinh T. Minh-ha's Reassemblage, Yvonne Rainer's Privilege—confirm this book's importance for readers in gender and cultural studies as well as for filmmakers and admirers of experimental writing, independent cinema, and the visual arts in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aExperimental filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion picture authorship. 0aMotion picture playsxHistory and criticism. 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 4acinema. 4afilm history. 4afilm. 4ascreen writing. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aavant garde films.  acinema.  acultural studies.  aexperimental film.  afilm criticism.  afilm history.  afilm scripts.  afilm.  afilmmaking.  afilmography.  agender studies.  agently down the stream.  ahollis frampton.  aindependent films.  alaura mulvey.  amorgan fisher.  amovies.  apeter wollen.  apoetic justice.  apressures of the text.  aprivilege.  areassemblage.  ariddles of the sphinx.  aseeing and reading.  aso is this.  astandard gauge.  asu friedrich.  asymbiopsychotaxiplasm.  atrinh t minh ha.  aunconventional film scripts.  awilliam greaves.  ayvonne rainer.  azorns lemma.1 aMacDonald, Scott, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cpr